Pop your #kettle{} on to boil. Halve, then remove the core from the @red pepper{1} and @yellow pepper{1/2} and cut into ½cm wide slices. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1} (stalks and all) and halve the @cherry tomatoes{1/2}. Zest the @lemon{1/2} with a #zester{}, then chop the lemon into wedges. Chop the @chestnut mushrooms{1} into 1cm chunks. Pick the @rosemary{2%sprigs} leaves from their stalks and finely chop (discard the stalks).

While you wait for your kettle to boil, heat a splash of oil in a #frying pan{} on high heat and add the chestnut mushrooms. They'll release water, so keep stirring and cooking them until this has evaporated and they are browned, ~{5%minutes}.

Add another splash of oil to the frying pan if it's dry and (still on high heat) add the peppers and cherry tomatoes. Stir together and cook until they have softened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Then, add in the garlic, rosemary leaves, @smoked paprika{1} and @ground turmeric{3/4%tsp}. Cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add half the parsley, the lemon zest and the @basmati rice{150%g} to your pan. Stir and cook everything for a few minutes so the rice can absorb the flavours in the pan.

Next, pour the boiling @water{300%ml} into a #measuring jug{} and stir in the @vegetable stock pot{1} to dissolve. Add this to the pan and give everything a good stir. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to medium-low and cover with a #lid{}. Cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from the heat and set aside (still covered) for another ~{10%minutes}.

> The rice will finish cooking in its own steam.

Once cooked, fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir in the remaining parsley. Taste and add a pinch of @salt{pinch}, a grind of @black pepper{} and a squeeze of lemon juice if you think it needs it. Serve the Spanish-style veggie rice with some lemon wedges on the side. Ándale!